President Donald Trump and members of the National Border Patrol Council held a press briefing to discuss the importance of border security and the need for a physical barrier, such as a wall, along the US-Mexico border. Trump congratulated Nancy Pelosi on being elected Speaker of the House and expressed hope for working together on issues like infrastructure. Border Patrol agents spoke about their personal experiences and the effectiveness of physical barriers in reducing illegal immigration and drug smuggling. They also emphasized their support for Trump and the need to secure the border. Trump thanked the agents for their work and reiterated the necessity of a wall for border security.